What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Pregabalin Market?

Market Analysis and Size

Pregabalin is an anticonvulsant medication that can be used to treat epilepsy, neuropathic pain, fibromyalgia, and generalized anxiety disorder. It works by reducing the pain signals delivered by injured nerves throughout the body. As per the International Association of the Study of Pain's Global Year against Neuropathic Pain 2014-2015 study, approximately 7% to 8% of adults suffer from chronic pain with neuropathic characteristics.

Data Bridge Market Research analyzes that the global pregabalin market which was USD 824.75 million in 2023, is likely to reach USD 1,088.56 million by 2031, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 3.53% during the forecast period. “Oral” dominates the dosage form segment of the market due to rising demand of pregabalin oral dosage form. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include depth expert analysis, patient epidemiology, pipeline analysis, pricing analysis, and regulatory framework.

